","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>CRUSHED FOOT</b> Can't run, only crawl. 3D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[42,42],"drawn":false},{"_id":"kWaDZTVfuNsC3upP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>CRUSHED ELBOW</b> Can’t use arm. 3D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[43,43],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8tRE9G7SghSyGnWJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>PUNCTURED LUNG</b> Fatal (1 day). STAMINA and MOBILITY –2. D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[44,44],"drawn":false},{"_id":"zWup9XY2DMQ8SiQZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>BLEEDING GUT</b> Fatal (1 day). One point of damage at every roll for MOBILITY and CLOSE COMBAT. D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[45,45],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RhQCyOObYow7F8US","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>RUPTURED INTESTINES</b> Fatal (1 shift). Disease with Virulence 6.  2D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[46,46],"drawn":false},{"_id":"M6CIT7eKdTYEbzdO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>BUSTED KIDNEY</b> Fatal (1 day). Can't run, only crawl, MOBILITY –2.  2D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[51,51],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ljYQ5lRgWaIYDf5K","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>ARM ARTERY CUT</b> Fatal -1 (1 turn). Can’t use arm. D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[52,52],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mbdBNWfDwsbitFQt","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>LEG ARTERY CUT</b> Fatal -1 (1 turn). To run becomes a slow action. D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[53,53],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lzGU4TK2LWf5GOiB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>SEVERED ARM</b> Fatal -1 (1 shift). Can't use arm. Permanent.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[54,54],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AEEYSvFWZTRz5kli","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>SEVERED LEG</b> Fatal -1 (1 shift). Can't run, only crawl. Permanent.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[55,55],"drawn":false},{"_id":"F3T3CVGfGqMHkLt7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>CRACKED SPINE</b> Paralyzed from the neck down. If not given MEDICAL AID in time, the effect is permanent. 3D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[56,56],"drawn":false},{"_id":"xLAXVkvzATGX1ViT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>RUPTURED JUGULAR</b> Fatal -1 (1 round). STAMINA -1. 2D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[61,61],"drawn":false},{"_id":"JGK9QRlaqvPgUaja","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>RUPTURED AORTA</b> Fatal -2 (1 round). STAMINA -2. 3D6 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[62,62],"drawn":false},{"_id":"dXgwNv8ns18ChRNh","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>DISEMBOWELED</b> Fatal. Instant death.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[63,63],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PAUEu4N9Ssmy5R7X","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>CRUSHED SKULL</b> Fatal. Your story ends here.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[64,64],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oQTNukOb5wBnryyj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>PIERCED HEART</b> Fatal. You die immediately.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[65,65],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fG1ucONDb9PQyDjT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>IMPALED HEART</b> Fatal. Your heart beats for the last time.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[66,66],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6*10+1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"OMeIJMoggfynRIHO","name":"Critical Injuries on Synthetics","permission":{"default":0,"q8HmJQOf882klbgH":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.qYbeyn1J6ahV4Kms"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"If a synthetic is Broken, roll for a critical injury on the table to the right. Until\r\nthe android suffers a System Shutdown, it can continue to operate, only suffering the effects of the critical injury. This makes androids very hard to stop. Each further attack inflicting damage on a Broken android will inflict another critical injury. \r\nIf you roll the same critical injury again, shift it down one step on the table (from a 4 to a 5, for example).","results":[{"_id":"TgLweWvbDfSpmGvX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>RUPTURED FLUID PUMP</b> The android loses its next slow action.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0VY5DZEKeBLJpoTc","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>DESTROYED LEG SERVOS</b> Both legs are non-functional. The android must stay prone and can only crawl.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"M0cRNcfIhCWUlJnE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>DESTROYED ARM SERVOS</b>  One arm is non-functional. The android can only use one-handed gear.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"vOUiK0AunK2dqPfC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>HEAD DISLOCATION</b> The android's artificial neck is severely fractured and its head placed in an unnatural position. All fast actions become slow actions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"px4aX3F2fsf8Od6M","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>SEVERE CHASSIS BREACH</b> Internal organs spill out and the android is completely immobilized.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ByP3UDNkS2NQ34iT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>SYSTEM SHUTDOWN</b> The android is torn to shreds or crushed. Core systems are severely damaged and a COMTECH roll is required to communicate with the android.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false}
{"_id":"mx5LFCLuDcKWs142","name":"Panic Table","permission":{"default":0,"q8HmJQOf882klbgH":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.NgPUmSwrD71eobxb"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"_id":"rNIEsETslgTE305N","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>KEEPING IT TOGETHER:</b> You manage to keep your nerves in check. Barely.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"kiO3yL2ptol7UFxN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>NERVOUS TWITCH:</b>  Your STRESS LEVEL, and the STRESS LEVEL of all friendly PCs in SHORT range of you, increases by one.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false},{"_id":"R1j5ZV1lZYOukzbO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>TREMBLE:</b>  You start to tremble uncontrollably. All skill rolls using AGILITY suffer a –2 modification until your panic stops.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"bVyaqMdKS03lMdeO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>DROP ITEM:</b>  Whether by stress, confusion or the realization that you’re all going to die anyway, you drop a weapon or other important item—the GM decides which one. Your STRESS LEVEL increases by one.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mDfxe7TR2QD2DCqj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>FREEZE:</b>  You’re frozen by fear or stress for one Round, losing your next slow action. Your STRESS LEVEL, and the STRESS LEVEL of all friendly PCs in SHORT range of you, increases by one","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5WPFiMValyy8lLBX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>SEEK COVER:</b>  You must use your next action to move away from danger and find a safe spot if possible. You are allowed to make a retreat roll (see page 93) if you have an enemy at ENGAGED range. Your STRESS LEVEL is decreased by one, but the STRESS LEVEL of all friendly PCs in SHORT range increases by one. After one Round, you can act normally.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WpWwS67NT6pnjP8Q","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>SCREAM:</b> You scream your lungs out for one Round, losing your next slow action. Your STRESS LEVEL is decreased by one, but every friendly character who hears your scream must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ru1oP3Z5EKK6rsH7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>FLEE:</b>  You just can’t take it anymore. You must flee to a safe place and refuse to leave it. You won’t attack anyone and won’t attempt anything dangerous. You are not allowed to make a retreat roll (see page 93) if you have an enemy at ENGAGED range when you flee. Your STRESS LEVEL is decreased by one, but every friendly character who sees you run must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[13,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"bG0AxhSq3jCNw5gf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>BERSERK:</b>  You must immediately attack the nearest person or creature, friendly or not. You won’t stop until you or the target is Broken. Every friendly character who witnesses your rampage must make an immediate Panic Roll","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[14,14],"drawn":false},{"_id":"90Vlsy8HGlJacGta","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>CATATONIC:</b>  You collapse to the floor and can’t talk or move, staring blankly into oblivion.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[15,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
